<subSubSection id="D9AD6543FFBBFFADD5DF8B29FF53FF23" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="9" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="910836C8FFBBFFADD5DF8B29FF53FF23" blockId="7.[151,1437,1806,2014]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1437,150,429]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="9" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis id="A3C3EADAFFBBFFA2D5DF8B29FEEEF895" bold="true" box="[199,324,1842,1868]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
This species differs from the other species of the family occurring in the freshwaters of the country (Atlantic) by the following combination of characters: absence of blue iridescent lines or spots below the eye [vs. present in 
<taxonomicName id="56B74D4BFFBBFFA2D4098B60FDD8F84C" authority="(Cuvier, 1828)" baseAuthorityName="Cuvier" baseAuthorityYear="1828" box="[273,626,1915,1941]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Lutjanidae" genus="Lutjanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="analis">
<emphasis id="A3C3EADAFFBBFFA2D4098B60FE6BF84C" box="[273,449,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Lutjanus analis</emphasis>
(Cuvier, 1828)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="56B74D4BFFBBFFA2D7B58B60FB91F84C" authority="(Linnaeus, 1758)" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[685,1083,1914,1941]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Lutjanidae" genus="Lutjanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="griseus">
<emphasis id="A3C3EADAFFBBFFA2D7B58B60FCC0F84D" box="[685,874,1915,1940]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Lutjanus griseus</emphasis>
(Linnaeus, 1758)
</taxonomicName>
]; absence of a black blotch on lateral line (vs. present in 
<taxonomicName id="56B74D4BFFBBFFA2D4DE8B84FD80F860" baseAuthorityName="Cuvier" baseAuthorityYear="1828" box="[454,554,1951,1977]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Lutjanidae" genus="Lutjanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="analis">
<emphasis id="A3C3EADAFFBBFFA2D4DE8B84FD80F860" box="[454,554,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">L. analis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); lateral line scales 47–51 (vs. 
<quantity id="564F9B2DFFBBFFA2D68D8B84FC51F860" box="[917,1019,1951,1977]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.143" metricValueMax="1.1938" metricValueMin="1.0922" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="in" value="45.0" valueMax="47.0" valueMin="43.0">43–47 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="56B74D4BFFBBFFA2D11C8B84FBDFF861" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[1028,1141,1951,1976]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Lutjanidae" genus="Lutjanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="griseus">
<emphasis id="A3C3EADAFFBBFFA2D11C8B84FBDFF861" box="[1028,1141,1951,1976]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">L. griseus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); gill rakers on the lower gill arch 14–16 [vs. 
<quantity id="564F9B2DFFBBFFA2D4678BD8FE4EF804" box="[383,484,1987,2013]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.302" metricValueMax="3.556" metricValueMin="3.048" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="in" value="13.0" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="12.0">12–14 in</quantity>
the other species); profile of anal fin angulate, with the middle rays prolonged [vs. rounded, without the middle rays prolonged in 
<taxonomicName id="56B74D4BFFB4FFADD7DB8C8CFC9CFF69" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[707,822,151,176]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Lutjanidae" genus="Lutjanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="griseus">
<emphasis id="A3C3EADAFFB4FFADD7DB8C8CFC9CFF69" box="[707,822,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">L. griseus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="56B74D4BFFB4FFADD66D8C8CFAF7FF68" authority="(Bloch &amp; Schneider, 1801)" baseAuthorityName="Bloch &amp; Schneider" baseAuthorityYear="1801" box="[885,1373,150,177]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Lutjanidae" genus="Lutjanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="jocu">
<emphasis id="A3C3EADAFFB4FFADD66D8C8CFBB8FF69" box="[885,1042,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Lutjanus jocu</emphasis>
(Bloch &amp; Schneider, 1801)
</taxonomicName>
]; and juveniles with a dark oblique stripe from snout through eye to top corner of operculum (not present in the other species).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D9AD6543FFB4FFADD5E68CC5FB43FEBF" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="materials_examined">
